dellNetLinkAggMib.name: dellNetLinkAggMib

revisions.description: Added support for LACP state monitoring and state change traps. 1. Added dot3aAggCfgLacpSupported, dot3aAggCfgOperStatus to dot3aAggConfigTable. 2. Added a new table dot3adAggPortTable for monitoring LACP state information per port. 3. Added textual convention DellNetLacpState for lacp state information and DellNetLacpKey for lacp key maintained at every physical port. 4. Added a notification dot3adAggLacpStateChange. 5. Modified alignment and description of some objects. 6. Deprecated dellNetLinkAggMibCompliance and added a new compliance statement dellNetLinkAggMibComplianceRev1. 7. Deprecated dellNetLinkAggCommonGroup and added a new object group dellNetLinkAggCommonGroupRev1. 8. Added two new object groups- - dellNetLinkAggPortGroup for the aggregator port table and - dellNetLinkAggNotificationGroup for the notification of lacp state change.

Dell Networking OS Link Aggregation MIB version 1.3. - Add FDB common table for configured or negotiated link aggregation. 1. Move textual conventions to the Textual-Convention MIB dellNet-tc.mib. 2. Rename dot3aClearCurAggFdb to dot3aClearFdb.
Dell Networking OS Link Aggregation MIB version 1.1. Deprecated dot3aAggStaticTable & dot3aAggFdbTable Added dot3aCurAggStaticTable & dot3aCurAggFdbTable because of indexing changes
First revision of Dell Networking OS link aggregation mib.
Dell Networking OS Link Aggregation MIB version 1.0.

dellNetLinkAggMib.description: Dell Networking OS Link Aggregation MIB.

DellNetLacpKey.name: DellNetLacpKey
DellNetLacpKey.description: The Actor or Partner Key value maintained by every port that is part of an aggregator.

DellNetLacpState.name: DellNetLacpState
DellNetLacpState.description: The Actor and Partner State values from the LACPDU.

dot3aAggConfigTable.name: dot3aAggConfigTable
dot3aAggConfigTable.description: A list of all aggregated links configured.

dot3aAggConfigEntry.name: dot3aAggConfigEntry
dot3aAggConfigEntry.description: A list of all aggregated links configured in the system

dot3aAggCfgId.name: dot3aAggCfgId
dot3aAggCfgId.description: The link aggregation id or port channel id.

dot3aAggCfgMacAddr.name: dot3aAggCfgMacAddr
dot3aAggCfgMacAddr.description: A 6-octet read only value MAC Address assigned to this link aggregation or user-defined MAC address if a static user-defined MAC address is configured.

dot3aAggCfgIfIndex.name: dot3aAggCfgIfIndex
dot3aAggCfgIfIndex.description: The logical interface index assigned to this link aggregation.

dot3aAggCfgNumPorts.name: dot3aAggCfgNumPorts
dot3aAggCfgNumPorts.description: The number of physical ports configured to this link aggregation. Maximum is 16 ports

dot3aAggCfgPortList.name: dot3aAggCfgPortList
dot3aAggCfgPortList.description: The bitmask of ports configured for this link aggregation. This object is deprecated and no longer in use. Please use the new dot3aAggCfgPortListString object instead.

dot3aAggCfgPortListString.name: dot3aAggCfgPortListString
dot3aAggCfgPortListString.description: The list of ports configured for this link aggregation. The format of this output is as follows: <interface type> <slot/port>, or <port channel> <number>

dot3aAggCfgLacpSupported.name: dot3aAggCfgLacpSupported
dot3aAggCfgLacpSupported.description: This object contains information about whether the link aggregation uses IEEE 802.3ad (Link Aggregation Control Protocol). true - indicates the Aggregation link uses LACP protocol. false - indicates the aggregation link is a statically configured link.

dot3aAggCfgOperStatus.name: dot3aAggCfgOperStatus
dot3aAggCfgOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the link aggregation. up - indicates the aggregated link is ready to transmit and receive network traffic. down - indicates there is some fault that prevents the aggregation link from going to the up(1) state.

dot3aAggStaticTable.name: dot3aAggStaticTable
dot3aAggStaticTable.description: A list of statically configured MAC Address on the aggregated links.

dot3aAggStaticEntry.name: dot3aAggStaticEntry
dot3aAggStaticEntry.description: A list of statically configured MAC Address on the aggregated links in the system

dot3aAggIndex.name: dot3aAggIndex
dot3aAggIndex.description: The link aggregation id or port channel id.

dot3aAggVlanId.name: dot3aAggVlanId
dot3aAggVlanId.description: VLAN id that this ports configured to .

dot3aAggMacAddr.name: dot3aAggMacAddr
dot3aAggMacAddr.description: A 6-octet read only value MAC Address assigned to this link aggregation or user-defined MAC address if a static user-defined MAC address is configured.

dot3aAggStatus.name: dot3aAggStatus
dot3aAggStatus.description: The status of this aggregation link . active - this aggregation link is active. inactive - this aggregation link is no active.

dot3aAggDistributedPort.name: dot3aAggDistributedPort
dot3aAggDistributedPort.description: The interface of the MAC address. The format of this output is as follows: <interface type> <slot/port>, or <port channel> <number>

dot3aAggFdbTable.name: dot3aAggFdbTable
dot3aAggFdbTable.description: A list of dynamically learned Mac Address on the aggregated links

dot3aAggFdbEntry.name: dot3aAggFdbEntry
dot3aAggFdbEntry.description: A list of dynamically learned Mac Address on the aggregated links in the system

dot3aAggFdbIndex.name: dot3aAggFdbIndex

dot3aAggFdbVlanId.name: dot3aAggFdbVlanId
dot3aAggFdbVlanId.description: The forwarding table VLAN id that this ports configured to .

dot3aAggFdbMacAddr.name: dot3aAggFdbMacAddr
dot3aAggFdbMacAddr.description: A 6-octet read only value MAC Address assigned to this link aggregation or user-defined MAC address if a static user-defined MAC address is configured.

dot3aAggFdbStatus.name: dot3aAggFdbStatus
dot3aAggFdbStatus.description: The status of this aggregation link . active - this aggregation link is active. inactive - this aggregation link is no active.

dot3aAggFdbDistributedPort.name: dot3aAggFdbDistributedPort
dot3aAggFdbDistributedPort.description: The interface of the MAC address. The format of this output is as follows: <interface type> <slot/port>, <port channel> <number>, or NULL if it is not available

dot3aCurAggStaticTable.description: A list of statically configured MAC Address on the aggregated links.

dot3aCurAggStaticEntry.name: dot3aCurAggStaticEntry
dot3aCurAggStaticEntry.description: A list of statically configured MAC Address on the aggregated links in the system

dot3aCurAggVlanId.name: dot3aCurAggVlanId
dot3aCurAggVlanId.description: This objects describes the VLAN id that this port is part of.

dot3aCurAggMacAddr.name: dot3aCurAggMacAddr
dot3aCurAggMacAddr.description: A 6-octet read only value MAC Address assigned to this link aggregation or user-defined MAC address if a static user-defined MAC address is configured.

dot3aCurAggIndex.name: dot3aCurAggIndex
dot3aCurAggIndex.description: The link aggregation id or port channel id.

dot3aCurAggStatus.name: dot3aCurAggStatus
dot3aCurAggStatus.description: The status of the static address configured on the aggregation link . active - the mac address is active. inactive - the mac address is not active.

dot3aCurAggFdbTable.name: dot3aCurAggFdbTable
dot3aCurAggFdbTable.description: A list of dynamically learned Mac Address on the aggregated links

dot3aCurAggFdbEntry.name: dot3aCurAggFdbEntry
dot3aCurAggFdbEntry.description: A list of dynamically learned Mac Address on the aggregated links in the system

dot3aCurAggFdbVlanId.name: dot3aCurAggFdbVlanId
dot3aCurAggFdbVlanId.description: This object gives information on the forwarding table VLAN id that this port is configured to .

dot3aCurAggFdbMacAddr.name: dot3aCurAggFdbMacAddr
dot3aCurAggFdbMacAddr.description: A 6-octet read only value MAC Address assigned to this link aggregation or user-defined MAC address if a static user-defined MAC address is configured.

dot3aCurAggFdbIndex.name: dot3aCurAggFdbIndex
dot3aCurAggFdbIndex.description: The FDB link aggregation id or port channel id.

dot3aCurAggFdbStatus.name: dot3aCurAggFdbStatus
dot3aCurAggFdbStatus.description: The status of this dynamic mac address learnt on the aggregation link . active - this mac address is active. inactive - this mac address is not active.

dot3aCommonAggFdbTable.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbTable
dot3aCommonAggFdbTable.description: A list of configured and dynamically negotiated aggregated links

dot3aCommonAggFdbEntry.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbEntry
dot3aCommonAggFdbEntry.description: A list of configured and dynamically negotiated aggregated links in the system

dot3aCommonAggFdbIndex.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbIndex
dot3aCommonAggFdbIndex.description: The FDB link aggregation id or port channel id.

dot3aCommonAggFdbVlanId.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbVlanId
dot3aCommonAggFdbVlanId.description: This object gives information about the VLAN id that the port channel is part of.

dot3aCommonAggFdbTagConfig.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbTagConfig
dot3aCommonAggFdbTagConfig.description: The status if the aggregation link is tagged, untagged, or not configured. tagged - this aggregation link is tagged. untagged - this aggregation link is untagged.

dot3aCommonAggFdbStatus.name: dot3aCommonAggFdbStatus
dot3aCommonAggFdbStatus.description: The status of the aggregation link in the vlan. active - when the aggregation link is up and part of vlan. inactive - when the aggregation link is down.

dot3adAggPortTable.name: dot3adAggPortTable
dot3adAggPortTable.description: A list of Link Aggregation Control configuration parameters for each Aggregation Port on this device.

dot3adAggPortEntry.name: dot3adAggPortEntry
dot3adAggPortEntry.description: List of aggregation control confirguration information per aggregated port in the system.

dot3adAggPortIndex.name: dot3adAggPortIndex
dot3adAggPortIndex.description: The ifIndex of the physical port that is part of an aggregator.

dot3adAggPortActorOperKey.name: dot3adAggPortActorOperKey
dot3adAggPortActorOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the Aggregation Port. The meaning of the particular Key values is of local significance.

dot3adAggPortPartnerOperKey.name: dot3adAggPortPartnerOperKey
dot3adAggPortPartnerOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the protocol Partner. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in the system if there is no protocol Partner.

dot3adAggPortActorAdminState.name: dot3adAggPortActorAdminState
dot3adAggPortActorAdminState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current administrative values of Actor_State as transmitted by the Actor in LACPDUs. The first bit corresponds to bit 0 of Actor_State (LACP_Activity), the second bit corresponds to bit 1 (LACP_Timeout), the third bit corresponds to bit 2 (Aggregation), the fourth bit corresponds to bit 3 (Synchronization), the fifth bit corresponds to bit 4 (Collecting), the sixth bit corresponds to bit 5 (Distributing), the seventh bit corresponds to bit 6 (Defaulted), and the eighth bit corresponds to bit 7 (Expired). These values allow administrative control over the values of LACP_Activity, LACP_Timeout and Aggregation.

dot3adAggPortActorOperState.name: dot3adAggPortActorOperState
dot3adAggPortActorOperState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current operational values of Actor_State as transmitted by the Actor in LACPDUs. The bit allocations are as defined in dot3adAggPortActorAdminState.

dot3adAggPortPartnerAdminState.name: dot3adAggPortPartnerAdminState
dot3adAggPortPartnerAdminState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current administrative value of Actor_State for the protocol Partner. The bit allocations are as defined in dot3adAggPortActorAdminState.

dot3adAggPortPartnerOperState.name: dot3adAggPortPartnerOperState
dot3adAggPortPartnerOperState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current values of Actor_State in the most recently received LACPDU transmitted by the protocol Partner. The bit allocations are as defined in dot3adAggPortActorAdminState. In the absence of an active protocol Partner, this value may reflect the manually configured value carried in the system.

dot3aClearFdb.name: dot3aClearFdb
dot3aClearFdb.description: Write yes(1) to this object will clear all fdb entries. The value will be changed to no(2) once the fdb is cleared. yes(1) - clear fdb aggregation links. no(2) - do not clear fdb aggregation links

dot3adAggLacpStateChange.name: dot3adAggLacpStateChange
dot3adAggLacpStateChange.description: The dot3adAggLacpStateChange indicates that the agent has detected a change in the Lacp state for one of the member ports of the aggregation link. This notification contains the information on the port which has gone through the state change and the oper state information of the actor and its partner.

linkBundleImbalanceClear.name: linkBundleImbalanceClear
